Lieutenant-Colonel, Charl Kinnear was shot dead outside his home in Bishop Lavis on Friday. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - The Bishop Lavis Community Policing Forum and the police's Anti-Gang Unit are holding a memorial service for murdered Lieutenant-Colonel Charl Kinnear, just hours after news of a breakthrough in the case. Kinnear was shot dead outside his home in Bishop Lavis on Friday. READ: Hawks target more arrests in Kinnear murder case The Hawks confirming earlier that a 39-year-old suspect has been arrested in connection with the assassination of the Anti-Gang Unit section commander. The man is yet to appear in court.